{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:45:03.387Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"agent_message","id":"amsg_019f7579-2c9b-7f02-9c5e-e4a0e7a8d7d9","author":"/root/harness_audit","recipient":"/root","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Message Type: FINAL_ANSWER\nTask name: /root\nSender: /root/harness_audit\nPayload:\nRead-only audit complete. The current runner has three benchmark defects:\n\n- Task timing starts at [run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:490](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:490), before any product indexing performed by Claude.\n- Graph `search` and `neighbors` do not share a reusable prebuilt index:\n  - `search` has no explicit cache directory and defaults to `syntax-only`.\n  - `neighbors` uses `$TMPDIR/entire-graph-cache` and defaults to `full`.\n  - More fundamentally, search caches query-selected `OnlyFiles` ([search.go:245](/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/search.go:245)), and `OnlyFiles` participates in the cache key ([search_cache.go:101](/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/search_cache.go:101)). A dummy search therefore does not warm a later task query.\n- The prompts force redundant work at [run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:258](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-repair-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:258): search, neighbors, then file-tool verification. CBM is explicitly told to index during the timed attempt at line 260.\n\n## Minimal patch design\n\n1. Add a global, unpaid setup phase before any Claude process starts.\n\n   `run()` should preflight every selected repository/treatment before entering the rotated execution loop at lines 725–750. If any setup fails, launch zero paid attempts.\n\n   Create:\n\n   ```python\n   prepare_treatment_index(repository, system, ...)\n   validate_treatment_index(repository, system, ...)\n   ```\n\n   Each writes `records/repo-N/system/setup.json` plus raw setup stdout/stderr. It records setup wall time, binary binding, checkout commit/tree, cache inventory hashes, and validation results.\n\n2. Entire Graph setup.\n\n   Use an isolated `graph-cache`, not the existing generic `cbm-cache`.\n\n   Prebuild the query-independent search cache:\n\n   ```text\n   entire-graph search\n     --repo CHECKOUT\n     --query __benchmark_preindex__\n     --format json\n     --head\n     --profile syntax-only\n     --index-all-files\n     --cache-dir GRAPH_CACHE\n   ```\n\n   Run it a second time and require:\n\n   - exit code zero;\n   - `commit == repository[\"commit\"]`;\n   - `tree == repository[\"tree\"]`;\n   - canonical `repo_root == checkout`;\n   - `profile == \"syntax-only\"`;\n   - `stats.index_cache_hit is true`.\n\n   Prebuild the separate full snapshot needed by `neighbors`:\n\n   ```text\n   entire-graph neighbors\n     --repo CHECKOUT\n     --symbol __benchmark_index_probe__\n     --format json\n     --head\n     --profile full\n     --cache-dir GRAPH_CACHE\n   ```\n\n   Run twice. Require the second invocation to leave the cache inventory byte-identical. Decode the generated gzip cache and require:\n\n   - `cache_version == \"search-snapshot-v1\"`;\n   - `provider_version == graph --version`;\n   - `tree == repository[\"tree\"]`;\n   - `profile == \"full\"`;\n   - snapshot header tree, provider, profile, and repository root all match.\n\n   The product should eventually expose cache-hit metadata for `neighbors`; decoding the cache is the minimal runner-only solution.\n\n3. Entire Graph timed commands.\n\n   Every Graph search command must use:\n\n   ```text\n   --head --profile syntax-only --index-all-files --cache-dir EXACT_GRAPH_CACHE\n   ```\n\n   Every neighbors command must use:\n\n   ```text\n   --head --profile full --cache-dir EXACT_GRAPH_CACHE\n   ```\n\n   This is necessary because ordinary query-dependent search keys cannot be generically prewarmed. Reject `--worktree`, `--no-cache`, another cache directory, or graph-streaming commands.\n\n4. CBM setup.\n\n   Use a deterministic project name such as `smoke-repo-01` and run, with `CBM_CACHE_DIR` set to the treatment cache:\n\n   ```text\n   codebase-memory-mcp cli index_repository\n     --repo-path CHECKOUT\n     --mode full\n     --name smoke-repo-01\n   ```\n\n   Require:\n\n   - exit code zero;\n   - JSON `status == \"indexed\"`;\n   - exact project name;\n   - `nodes > 0`;\n   - no `error`, degraded status, or integrity warning.\n\n   Then run:\n\n   ```text\n   codebase-memory-mcp cli index_status --project smoke-repo-01\n   codebase-memory-mcp cli list_projects\n   ```\n\n   Require no error/degraded/missing/corrupt result and exactly the expected project. Also require a nonempty database cache and an unchanged pristine checkout before and after indexing.\n\n   All three historical CBM attempts returned `status: degraded`, zero nodes, and an integrity-check removal. Under this corrected protocol the runner would abort before spending model money. A working/fixed comparator build is required before the next comparison.\n\n5. Move the task timer.\n\n   Only set `task_started = time.monotonic()` immediately before the Claude `run_command`. Store:\n\n   - `setup_wall_time_ms` in `setup.json`;\n   - `task_wall_time_ms` in the attempt record;\n   - setup record SHA-256 in the attempt record.\n\n   The scoreboard should label these separately as “Task wall time (pre-indexed)” and “Setup/index time (excluded).”\n\n6. Replace the treatment prompts.\n\n   Graph prompt:\n\n   > Entire Graph is already indexed and validated. Make at least one successful Entire Graph retrieval call, choosing search or neighbors according to the question. Use additional Graph calls or targeted file reads only when useful; do not automatically duplicate Graph results with file tools.\n\n   CBM prompt:\n\n   > CBM project `smoke-repo-01` is already indexed and validated. Use at least one retrieval tool against that project. Do not invoke `index_repository`.\n\n7. Replace the compliance audit at lines 436–453.\n\n   Graph compliance should accept either successful search or successful neighbors; it must not require both. Audit every Graph command for the exact HEAD/profile/cache flags above.\n\n   CBM compliance should:\n\n   - reject timed `index_repository` and `delete_project`;\n   - require a successful retrieval operation such as `search_graph`, `query_graph`, `trace_path`, `get_code_snippet`, `get_architecture`, or `search_code`;\n   - require the exact preindexed project;\n   - not count `index_status` or `list_projects` alone as treatment use.\n\n## Required tests\n\nReplace the existing neighbors-required test at [test_run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:124](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-repair-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/test_run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:124) and add tests covering:\n\n- search-only and neighbors-only Graph treatments both comply;\n- no Graph retrieval fails;\n- wrong cache, missing `--head`, missing `--index-all-files`, wrong profile, and `--no-cache` fail;\n- Graph setup rejects tree/profile/version mismatch and a second-search cache miss;\n- CBM setup accepts an indexed nonempty project;\n- the historical CBM `status: degraded` response fails before Claude launch;\n- timed CBM reindexing fails compliance;\n- setup failure for any selected arm results in zero paid executions;\n- task timing excludes a deliberately long mocked setup;\n- summary reports setup and task time separately;\n- a synthetic legacy schema-1 evidence directory is rejected without changing any byte.\n\n## Frozen evidence protection\n\nAdd `measurement_protocol: \"preindexed-agentic-v2\"` to new execution configurations. Before any write, reject a nonempty output directory whose config lacks that exact protocol. The corrected run must use a new output directory; never point it at `/private/tmp/oracle-agentic-overlay-smoke`.\n\nDo not change the existing 20260718 authorization, recovery, diagnostic JSON/Markdown, transcripts, records, or scoreboard. The existing authorization explicitly says reruns are false and binds the old runner hash.\n\nI made no repository changes and launched no paid agents. The benchmark worktree remains clean."}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
