{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:46:36.197Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The audit found four product-level causes of avoidable benchmark work beyond the original Zod bug: no explicit preindex command, no auditable neighbor cache hit, Cartesian path expansion in agent output, and no way to exclude external/test edges for a production-only question. I’m implementing those as general product capabilities now, in parallel, with separate file ownership.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:46:36.197Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","id":"msg_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b83bc141881918e3f8984a361f292","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The audit found four product-level causes of avoidable benchmark work beyond the original Zod bug: no explicit preindex command, no auditable neighbor cache hit, Cartesian path expansion in agent output, and no way to exclude external/test edges for a production-only question. I’m implementing those as general product capabilities now, in parallel, with separate file ownership."}],"phase":"commentary","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
