{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:59:55.113Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b86db11cc8191bf3d2e547975c690","status":"completed","call_id":"call_X28Ey2j1yVF2fAaSUN6OjlIE","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/oracle-agentic-overlay/methodology-correction-20260718.md\\n+# Preindexed Agentic Measurement Correction\\n+\\n+The completed `20260718` compiler-oracle smoke remains immutable diagnostic\\n+evidence. Its transcripts, raw records, authorization, recovery record,\\n+scoreboard, and diagnostic report are not rescored or rewritten by this\\n+correction.\\n+\\n+## Invalidated comparison\\n+\\n+The historical wall-time comparison is invalid. The timed Entire Graph arm was\\n+required to run an uncached selective `search` and a separately cached full\\n+`neighbors` build. One Zod attempt also invoked `neighbors` without `--head`,\\n+which forced another worktree build. The CBM arm was instructed to index during\\n+the task and repeatedly returned a degraded index. These setup costs were inside\\n+the agent timer and competed across concurrent attempts.\\n+\\n+The historical prompt also forced Entire Graph to use `search`, then\\n+`neighbors`, then file-tool verification. The file-tools arm had no comparable\\n+minimum workflow. Consequently, task latency cannot be repaired by subtracting\\n+a single observed indexing duration.\\n+\\n+Raw transcript facts such as returned answers, provider token billing, and tool\\n+calls remain useful diagnostics of that exact treatment. They are not clean\\n+causal estimates for the repaired product or corrected protocol.\\n+\\n+## Replacement protocol\\n+\\n+New runs use `preindexed-agentic-v2` and a new output directory.\\n+\\n+1. Materialize and verify the exact committed repository tree.\\n+2. Build each product index before any paid agent process starts.\\n+3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, profile, and\\n+   isolated cache. Any missing, degraded, corrupt, or cache-miss state aborts\\n+   the whole run before a paid attempt launches.\\n+4. Record setup/index duration separately from task duration.\\n+5. Give each product arm symmetric instructions: use its assigned preindexed\\n+   retrieval system as primary, choose the appropriate retrieval call, and use\\n+   targeted file reads only when useful. Do not force duplicate verification.\\n+6. Require timed Entire Graph calls to use the validated committed-tree cache;\\n+   reject worktree builds, alternate caches, cache misses, and no-cache calls.\\n+7. Reject CBM indexing or project mutation during a timed task.\\n+8. Run attempts without concurrent local indexing. Report cached retrieval and\\n+   end-to-end agent latency separately from setup and incremental-update cost.\\n+\\n+The corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\\n+execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`.\\n+\\n+## Claim boundary\\n+\\n+The same three repositories are a development regression smoke only. They can\\n+verify that diagnosed defects no longer recur, but they cannot support a broad\\n+superiority claim after the outcomes have been observed. A claim requires a\\n+fresh, outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen product and comparator heads,\\n+explicit semantics for abstract declarations, constructors, generated mirrors,\\n+and repeated paired attempts.\\n+\\n+No paid rerun is authorized by this correction.\\n*** Update File: /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/oracle-agentic-overlay/README.md\\n@@\\n # Compiler-Oracle Agentic Overlay\\n+\\n+The completed 2026-07-18 smoke is diagnostic-only. Its wall-time comparison\\n+included product indexing and is invalid; see\\n+[`methodology-correction-20260718.md`](methodology-correction-20260718.md) for\\n+the immutable-evidence boundary and the replacement preindexed protocol.\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
